ciscoLS1010ChassisMIB.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisMIB

revisions.description: -Added enum ACL Daughter card SubModuleType for Cat8540. -Added enum for TS Carrier Module. -Added enum for medium SingleModeLRFiber for OC3 and OC12 ATM pams.

-Added object for module hardware minor version. -Added objects for module and submodule serial number in string format. -Deprecated integer serial number objects for module and submodule. -Added enumeration to submodule type for NRP2 for 6400. -Reduce to single Module Compliance for clarity.
Added enums XPIF GE, ATM, and POS SubModuleTypes for Cat8540c. Added enums cmpmCarrier ModuleType for Cat8540c.
Added enums in ChassisSysType & ChassisBkplType for Cat4908g
Added enums for OC48c LR, and Dual Slot modules.
Added enums for OC48c and ARM modules.
Added enums in ChassisSysType & ChassisBkplType for C2948.
Added enums in subModuleType for the IMA & ATM25M4P PAMs.
Consolidate changes from C6400, C8500, FR-PAM, new modules.
Added new enum c8510. Also new tables for enet ports and LEDs.
Added a new PsType for -48 VDC.
Initial version of this MIB module.

OperStatus.name: OperStatus
OperStatus.description: Operational status of a chassis component. fanAlarm(4) is only applicable to the C5500 power supply. A fault(3) supercedes a fanAlarm(4). partialFault(5) & empty(6) are used by the Cisco6400 for the fan status to indicate partial fans failure & fan not present. A fault(3) value indicates total fans failure in the C6400.

AdminStatus.name: AdminStatus
AdminStatus.description: Admin status of a chassis component.

ciscoLS1010ChassisPs0Led.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisPs0Led
ciscoLS1010ChassisPs0Led.description: LED Status of power supply number 1.

ciscoLS1010ChassisPs1Led.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisPs1Led
ciscoLS1010ChassisPs1Led.description: LED Status of power supply number 2.

ciscoLS1010ChassisEnetLinkLed.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisEnetLinkLed
ciscoLS1010ChassisEnetLinkLed.description: Ethernet link status LED of CPU card.

ciscoLS1010ChassisTempStatus.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisTempStatus
ciscoLS1010ChassisTempStatus.description: The chassis temperature status. The values of minorWarning(3), majorWarning(4) and criticalWarning(5) will be primarily used by C6400 to indicate the core temperature. C6400 will never report overTemperature(2) status. In C6400 there are two temperature sensors: core and inlet. C6400 use this object to represent the core temperature and the other object ciscoLS1010ChassisInletTempStatus to represent the inlet temperature.

ciscoLS1010ChassisNumSlots.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisNumSlots
ciscoLS1010ChassisNumSlots.description: The number of slots in the chassis for plug-in modules.

ciscoLS1010ChassisLastChange.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisLastChange
ciscoLS1010ChassisLastChange.description: The last time chassis physical content get changed.

ciscoLS1010ChassisFailureAction.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisFailureAction
ciscoLS1010ChassisFailureAction.description: The action to take when there is any chassis failure, which includes either power supply, voltage, temperature and fan failure.

ciscoLS1010ChassisChangeAction.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisChangeAction
ciscoLS1010ChassisChangeAction.description: The action to take when there is any chassis change, which includes either power supply, fan and boards.

ciscoLS1010ChassisClockingMode.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisClockingMode
ciscoLS1010ChassisClockingMode.description: The clocking mode of the ls1010 system. By default, the mode is non-revertive, which means that the clock will stick to the current priority, even though higher priority clock is available.

ciscols1010SystemClockSourceStatus.name: ciscols1010SystemClockSourceStatus
ciscols1010SystemClockSourceStatus.description: The network clock source status of 'system' source: 'notSelected' indicates 'system' not selected as the network clock source. 'selected' indicates ASP freerunning(system) is selected as network clock source.

ciscols1010SystemClockSourcePriority.name: ciscols1010SystemClockSourcePriority
ciscols1010SystemClockSourcePriority.description: The highest priority at which 'system' is configured as a network clock source.

ciscoLS1010ChassisInletTempStatus.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisInletTempStatus
ciscoLS1010ChassisInletTempStatus.description: C6400 has two temperature sensors: core and inlet. C6400 use this object to represent the inlet temperature and use the object ciscoLS1010ChassisTempStatus to represent the core temperature.

ciscoLS1010ModuleTable.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleTable
ciscoLS1010ModuleTable.description: A list of module entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ciscoLS1010ChassisNumSlots.

ciscoLS1010ModuleEntry.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleEntry
ciscoLS1010ModuleEntry.description: Entry containing information about one module in a slot of the chassis.

ciscoLS1010ModuleIndex.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleIndex
ciscoLS1010ModuleIndex.description: A unique value for each module.

ciscoLS1010ModuleSerialNumber.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleSerialNumber
ciscoLS1010ModuleSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the module. Deprecated in favor of object ciscoLS1010ModuleSerialNumberString. This object returns 0 for modules using an alphanumeric numbering scheme.

ciscoLS1010ModuleHwVersion.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleHwVersion
ciscoLS1010ModuleHwVersion.description: The hardware version of the module.

ciscoLS1010ModuleDescr.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleDescr
ciscoLS1010ModuleDescr.description: A descriptive string used by the agent to describe the module.

ciscoLS1010ModuleNumSubModules.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleNumSubModules
ciscoLS1010ModuleNumSubModules.description: The max number of sub-modules supported by this module.

ciscoLS1010ModuleAdminStatus.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleAdminStatus
ciscoLS1010ModuleAdminStatus.description: This object, when read, always returns a value of ok(1). Setting this object to one of the acceptable values gives the following results: reset: reset the module's control logic enable: enable the module disable: disable the module Setting this object to any other values results in an error.

ciscoLS1010ModuleHwVersionMinor.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleHwVersionMinor
ciscoLS1010ModuleHwVersionMinor.description: The minor hardware version of the module.

ciscoLS1010ModuleSerialNumberString.name: ciscoLS1010ModuleSerialNumberString
ciscoLS1010ModuleSerialNumberString.description: The serial number of the module.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleTable.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleTable
ciscoLS1010SubModuleTable.description: A list of sub-module entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ciscoLS1010SlotNumSubModules.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleEntry.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleEntry
ciscoLS1010SubModuleEntry.description: Entry containing information about one sub-module in a sub-slot of the module.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleIndex.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleIndex
ciscoLS1010SubModuleIndex.description: A unique value for each sub-module within the module. This value is determined by sub-slot number where the sub-module is inserted.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleSerialNumber.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleSerialNumber
ciscoLS1010SubModuleSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the sub-module. Deprecated in favor of object ciscoLS1010SubModuleSerialNumberString. This object returns 0 for submodules using an alphanumeric numbering scheme.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersion.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersion
ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersion.description: The major hardware version of the sub-module. Together with ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersionMinor, this completely specifies the hardware version of the sub-module.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleDescr.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleDescr
ciscoLS1010SubModuleDescr.description: A descriptive string used by the agent to describe the module.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleNumPorts.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleNumPorts
ciscoLS1010SubModuleNumPorts.description: The maximum number of ports supported by this sub-module.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleAdminStatus.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleAdminStatus
ciscoLS1010SubModuleAdminStatus.description: This object can be read/written as reset or ok.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersionMinor.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersionMinor
ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersionMinor.description: The minor hardware version of the sub-module. Together with ciscoLS1010SubModuleHwVersion, this completely specifies the hardware version of the sub-module.

ciscoLS1010SubModuleSerialNumberString.name: ciscoLS1010SubModuleSerialNumberString
ciscoLS1010SubModuleSerialNumberString.description: The serial number of the sub-module.

ciscoLS1010PortTable.name: ciscoLS1010PortTable
ciscoLS1010PortTable.description: A list of port entries. The number of entries is determined by the number of modules in the chassis, the number of sub-module in the module and the number of ports on each sub-module.

ciscoLS1010PortEntry.name: ciscoLS1010PortEntry
ciscoLS1010PortEntry.description: Entry containing information for a particular port on a sub-module.

ciscoLS1010PortIndex.name: ciscoLS1010PortIndex
ciscoLS1010PortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies this port within a sub-module. The value is determined by the location of the port on the sub-module. Valid entries are 1 to the value of subModuleNumPorts for this sub-module.

ciscoLS1010PortIfIndex.name: ciscoLS1010PortIfIndex
ciscoLS1010PortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value assigned to this port.

clsEnetPortTable.name: clsEnetPortTable
clsEnetPortTable.description: A list of ethernet port entries. This table is mainly to support ethernet port only.

clsEnetPortEntry.name: clsEnetPortEntry
clsEnetPortEntry.description: Entry contains information of a particular ethernet port.

clsEnetPortDuplex.name: clsEnetPortDuplex
clsEnetPortDuplex.description: Indicates whether the port is operating in half-duplex, full-duplex, or auto mode. If the port could not agree with the far end on port duplex, the port will be in auto(2) mode. Unknown(1) indicates either the port does not support duplex mode, or the duplex mode is none of the defined.

clsEnetPortAdminSpeed.name: clsEnetPortAdminSpeed
clsEnetPortAdminSpeed.description: Indicates the desired speed of the port in bits per second. The current operational speed of the port is determined by ifSpeed. If the port could not agree with the far end on port speed, the port will be in auto(2) mode, which will force the port to transmit in speed whichever is lower. Unknown(1) indicates either the port does not support admin speed, or the admin speed is none of the defined.

clsEnetPortType.name: clsEnetPortType
clsEnetPortType.description: The type of physical layer medium-dependent interface on the port. unknown(1) indicates that the port type is none of those defined. empty(6) indicates that the port is not present.

clsEnetPortLinkStatus.name: clsEnetPortLinkStatus
clsEnetPortLinkStatus.description: This object indicates how the link status of the port came up. autoNegotiate(2) -- the port will try to negotiate the link with the partner port. If successful, the link will come up, otherwise the link will remain down. forceUp(3) -- the port will force the link up irrespective of its partner port. This will bring up the link in full duplex only. Default is autoNegotiate(2).

clsPortLedTable.name: clsPortLedTable
clsPortLedTable.description: A list of LED entries associated with a port.

clsPortLedEntry.name: clsPortLedEntry
clsPortLedEntry.description: Entry contains information of a particular LED associated with a particular port which is identified by ifIndex.

clsPortLedIndex.name: clsPortLedIndex
clsPortLedIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies this LED among all the LEDs associated with the port identified by ifIndex. This value is related to the physical location of the LED, and is in ascending order from top to bottom, left to right.

clsPortLedType.name: clsPortLedType
clsPortLedType.description: Indicates the type or label of the LED.

clsPortLedStatus.name: clsPortLedStatus
clsPortLedStatus.description: Indicates the status of the LED. Unknown(1) indicates either the LED status is not supported or the status is none of the defined.

ciscoAtmCpuAdminStatus.name: ciscoAtmCpuAdminStatus
ciscoAtmCpuAdminStatus.description: Reset will reload the CPU board.

ciscoAtmSwitchTotalBuffer.name: ciscoAtmSwitchTotalBuffer
ciscoAtmSwitchTotalBuffer.description: The total cell buffer count in switch's shared memory.

ciscoAtmSwitchFreeBuffer.name: ciscoAtmSwitchFreeBuffer
ciscoAtmSwitchFreeBuffer.description: The free cell buffer count in switch's shared memory.

ciscoAtmSwitchDiscardCells.name: ciscoAtmSwitchDiscardCells
ciscoAtmSwitchDiscardCells.description: The total discarded cells of the switch.

ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCells.name: ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCells
ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCells.description: The total invalid cells of the switch.

ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderTable.name: ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderTable
ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderTable.description: A list of invalid cell header entries.

ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderEntry.name: ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderEntry
ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderEntry.description: a entry of invalid cell header.

ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderIndex.name: ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderIndex
ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeaderIndex.description: A sequence number that identifies a invalid cell header entry in the table.

ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeader.name: ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeader
ciscoAtmSwitchInvalidCellHeader.description: The most recently received invalid cells header. octet 0 is port number (0-32), octet 1 bit 7-5 is PTI, octet 1 bit 4 is CLP, octet 1 bit 3-0 is GFC, octet 2 is VPI, octet 3 is high byte of VCI octet 4 is low byte of VCI.

ciscoAtmCpuTerminateOamFlow.name: ciscoAtmCpuTerminateOamFlow
ciscoAtmCpuTerminateOamFlow.description: Terminate all the incoming OAM cells to the CPU port.

ciscoAtmInterceptEndToEndOamFlow.name: ciscoAtmInterceptEndToEndOamFlow
ciscoAtmInterceptEndToEndOamFlow.description: Indicates whether incoming end-to-end OAM flow cells are sent to the switch CPU. If the value is 'true', all incoming end-to-end OAM flow cells, including those on transit connections, are sent to the switch CPU. This value may be modified at any time. The modified value will apply to all existing connections. Note that if the value is 'false', the switch can not use the ATM PING application for end-to-end loopback on transit connections, since the end-to-end OAM cells on such connections will not be seen by the switch CPU.

ciscoLS1010ChassisFailureNotification.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisFailureNotification
ciscoLS1010ChassisFailureNotification.description: Agent detects a change in the status of ps0, ps1, fan, 12V line, and/or chassis temperature. This notification will be generated when the status changes from no-fault to fault, and also when the status changes from fault to no-fault.

ciscoLS1010ChassisChangeNotification.name: ciscoLS1010ChassisChangeNotification
